messages.message: Yes, this was in a fresh stack while it was warming up.. While modern web pages download several Mbs of data, it is mostly images or media... Js, css and other static files are almost always compressed for optimal page loads, hence raised the question.

if `server-nginx` is serving MB-sized javascript bundles, then there’s something mis-configured with `server-nginx` in this deployment

are you still seeing the large file size and slow load time in these SaaS environments after they’ve fully come up?
